    "body": "<!--\r\n  Thank you for contributing to Neovim!\r\n  If this is your first time, check out https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#pull-requests-prs\r\n  for our PR guidelines.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n`parser_gc()` calls `ts_parser_delete()` but leaves the userdata pointer pointing to freed memory. If the GC finalizer runs at an unexpected time (e.g. inside `nvim_buf_get_lines` as seen in #39411), a stale pointer could cause a crash.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n- NULL out `*ud` after `ts_parser_delete()` in `parser_gc()`\r\n- Update `parser_check()` to handle NULL with a clear error message, guarding all parser methods against UAF\r\n\r\nFixes #39411\r\n\r\nDraft - opening to run CI and discuss approach before requesting review.",
    "closed_at": null,
